            <section ID="s3">
               <id root="aa073085-fce4-410a-93d4-36844b792b43"/>
               <code code="34089-3" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="DESCRIPTION SECTION"/>
               <title>DESCRIPTION
</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>Hydralazine Hydrochloride Injection, USP is an antihypertensive available in a 1 mL vial for intravenous and<br/>intramuscular administration. Hydralazine Hydrochloride Injection, USP is a sterile, nonpyrogenic colorless solution.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <content styleCode="bold">Each mL contains</content>:</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <content styleCode="bold">Active</content>: Hydralazine Hydrochloride, USP, 20 mg<br/>
                     <content styleCode="bold">Preservatives</content>: Methylparaben, NF, 0.65 mg; Propylparaben, NF, 0.35 mg<br/>
                     <content styleCode="bold">Inactives</content>: Propylene Glycol, USP, 103.6 mg; Sodium Hydroxide and/or Hydrochloric Acid to adjust pH (3.4 to 4.4)<br/>and Water for Injection.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <br/>Hydralazine Hydrochloride, USP is 1-hydrazinophthalazine monohydrochloride, and its structural formula is:</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <renderMultiMedia referencedObject="Lde611474-4cd7-420c-9f0b-287fd8c3c9d9"/>
                  </paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Molecular Formula C<sub>8</sub>H<sub>8</sub>N<sub>4</sub>•HCl</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <br/>Hydralazine Hydrochloride, USP is a white to off-white, odorless crystalline powder. It is soluble in water, slightly<br/>soluble in alcohol, and very slightly soluble in ether. It melts at about 275°C, with decomposition, and has a molecular<br/>weight of 196.64.</paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20250603"/>
